The World Health Organisation ( WHO ) will hold a consultation and planning meeting on accelerated support for malaria prevention and control in the region between November 17 to 21 in Harare
The Philippines has made a big stride in malaria control with malaria infections rate in the country is now generally low
The Yunnan Institute of Malaria Prevention , China's only malaria research organ of its kind , established in 1957 , has trained more than 2,000 personnel in malaria prevention and treatment
Malaria is spreading quickly in sub-Saharan Africa as a result of deforestation continues to be one of the most serious public health problems and a major obstacle to social and economic development in southern Africa causes an estimated 300 to 300 million acute cases per year , with most deaths occurring among children in Africa
Drug combinations for multi-drug resistance malaria and vaccines against malaria are being developed at the global level while insecticide-treated mosqui nets and curtains have emerged in recent years as a promising tool to prevent malaria disease
The conference this week in Abuja , Nigeria , is sponsored by the World Health Organization and will draw together U.N. agencies , the World Bank , Western donors and the heads of 20 African countries in a Roll Back Malaria campaign that hopes to halve deaths from malaria , a mosquito-borne disease , within 10 years
The targets adopted by the meeting included reduction of malaria mortality by 50 percent by the year 2010 , and reduce by at least half the socio-economic negatives of malaria
